  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_a2">
    <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
<p>Sarah Robinson Fay Swift (1751-1804) was born on November 13, 1751 in Hardwick, Massachusetts to Samuel and Mercy Robinson, and removed with her family to Bennington, Vermont as a young woman. In Bennington, she married an attorney named Benjamin Fay, who passed away in 1786. Following his death, she married Heman Swift of Cornwall, and subsequently moved to his hometown. Sarah was Heman’s third wife, and was killed in a lightning strike at their home on April 17, 1804.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_a3">
    <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
<p>The majority of items in this collection are letters sent to Sarah from her family in Vermont, including children from her first marriage, after she moved to Connecticut.</p>  </scopecontent>
